  "title": "Operations Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>Provide technical support and able to troubleshoot breakdowns</p><p>Review and/or undertake preventive and corrective maintenance</p><p>Liaise closely with client representatives on all service/maintenance related issues</p><p>Attend to emergency calls during office hours and standby duties after office hours</p><p>Respond quickly if any technical faults, power trip, aircon breakdown, water leaking even at nights</p><p>Ensure that works carried out are in compliance with the Workplace Safety and Health Act.</p><p>Perform any other technical tasks when required</p><p>Able to work night shifts, including Weekends and Public holidays if necessary.</p><p><strong>Job requirements:</strong></p><p>GCE ‘O’ level and above</p><p>Minimum 2 years of relevant technical experience</p><p>Good interpersonal and problem solving skills</p><p>Independent, self-motivated individual whom is able to work under minimum supervision</p><p>Interested candidates who wish to apply for the advertised position, please click on “Apply Now”.</p>",
